<font size="+2">P.S:
</font>
Years later, Jerry Falwell complained that his famous 9/11 rave was
taken out of context. Al Franken said that the only way it could be
considered to have been taken
out of context was if it were immediately preceded by the words,<br>
<center>
<font size="+2" color="#cf0000" face="Courier,Helvetica,Arial">
&quot;I'd have to be a friggin' nut to say...&quot;<br>
</font>
== Al Franken Show, Air America Radio, 1 December 2004.
</center>
